reviewText: There are only 3 other reviews written for this, one of them very poorly reviewed, the other overly harsh, and the other rather fair.  I think even without comparing this event to a WWE event, this stands out as a great event, and something of a phenomenal start for TNA's 3 hour pay per views.20 Man X Division GauntletThe best word for this match is phenomenal.  A lot of TNA originals are featured, as well as imports from Japan and Mexico, and unlike most battle royals (or Royal Rumbles) this one was non-stop wrestling action from start to finish.  So much was going on, it was even more amazing that the superstars managed to so fluidly shift the centers of action.  (10/10)The Naturals, Kid Kash, and Dallas vs Ron Killings, Eric Watts, Johnny B. Badd, and Pat KenneyI barely remembered this match, so clearly it wasn't very memorable.  (1/10)Piratita Morgan vs Mascarita SagradaIf these men are prime examples of midget wrestling, then I think midget wrestling has been grossly underrated and mocked.  Despite their small sizes, they worked phenomenally with each other, like normal-sized luchadores, and while it wasn't a great match, it was certainly a good one, and something special to watch.  (7/10)NWA Tag Team ChampionshipTeam Canada (C) vs 3 Live KruWithout Ron Killings on their team, I didn't expect anything from 3 Live Kru.  I was surprised a bit by Konnan, who showed some good power and strength during his time in the ring, but most of this match was about Team Canada, who did fairly well against them.  (5/10)Trinity vs JacquelineI guess this was Jacqueline's debut in TNA?  Either way, it wasn't so much a match as just an interference in Trinity's glory-hounding.Monster's Ball MatchMonty Brown vs Raven vs AbyssThe hype behind this was rather ridiculous, trying to make us think the three were locked in a dark room without food or water for 24 hours.  The match itself was less than memorable, but the superstars definitely showed off greatly, and Monty Brown greatly sold his powerful slight-monster gimmick.  (6.5/10)X Division ChampionshipPetey Williams (C) vs AJ StylesAnd this match shows why they call AJ Styles Phenomenal.  With the short time they had, they crammed the match full of wrestling and high-flying moves fit for a classic bout.  It was beautiful, brilliant, and phenomenal.  (10/10)Triple X vs America's Most WantedI have no idea where or why another reviewer called this match a sloppy mess.  This battle was brutally fought, with plenty of hard spots, and great high-flying and technical wrestling, featuring some of the best wrestling by these two teams I've seen, better even than their cage match at Turning Point the next month.  (9/10)NWA World Heavyweight ChampionshipJeff Jarrett (C) vs Jeff HardyFor a ladder match, this was both bad and good.  Bad in that the men were sloppy in some places, botching a few moves, good in that they made these messes look good, and never slowed down like in some ladder matches to have time-wasting pillowstrike brawls.  It was constantly moving, and perhaps that was why it appeared sloppy at times.  Sure, Nash's heel turn was predictable, but still fun to see.  (8/10)Despite what others say, I have to say this was a phenomenal event, displaying the best (and not so best) that TNA has to offer.
summary: Phenomenal start for TNA's 3 Hour runs

reviewText: This is one of the very first TNA PPV's to be released on dvd.20 Man X Division Gauntlet: I dont really remember this. Even though it was one of the only reasons to watch TNA in 2004 and 2005.The Naturals, Kid Kash, and Dallas VS Ron Killings, Eric Watts, Johnny B. Badd, and Pat Kenney: Just like today, TNA tries to stuff to many men into one match. This was when TNA looked like a newer version of WCW. I mean Eric Watts? Johnny B. Badd? Thats old school WCW. Pat Kenney was Disco Inferno.Piratita Morgan VS Mascarita Sagrada: I dont mind this match. It just seemed TNA was trying to make a good first impression on first time viewers.Team Canada VS 3 Live Kru: Team Canada never lost on a PPV when they held the tag titles or were wrestling to win the tag titles. I always hated that.Trinity VS Jacqueline: X-Division, midget wrestling, a 6 man tag team match, tag team wrestling, and now a womens match. What will they think of next? No really. This PPV is getting really boring and fast.Monty Brown VS Raven VS Abyss: The first Monster's Ball match. While it should have been a high point to this PPV, it really wasnt. Good match though.Petey Williams VS AJ Styles: This is way we call it PPV. A match that people will actully pay to see. This match was amazing in every sense of the word. Scott D'Amore did bring it down a bit with outside interference but still an awesome match.Triple X VS America's Most Wanted: One thing I can say about TNA in the early years, they had some great tag team matches. This was a very good match to a great feud.Jeff Hardy VS Jeff Jarrett: What a waste of talent. Hardy was misused in TNA that is laughable. Sure he got a title shot but then again, what former WWE star didnt in TNA? The end of this match really sucks. The guitar shots are so weak that im surprised Hardy sold them. Im glad Hardy went back to WWE because TNA treated him like crap.A very bad PPV. They tried every match they could think of on this one and most of them failed. Expect for a couple matches, then this PPV isnt worth it at all. Then again you could get the only good matches on other TNA dvd releases.

reviewText: TNA's first PPV came during the booking era of Dusty Rhodes (who's currently a booker in WWE) so there are alot of hits & misses on this event.20 Man X Division Gauntlet (Royal Rumble style match) - The format is similar to the Royal Rumble except only 20 guys & short time interluded. You'll see old favorites like Spanky, Psychosis, La Parka, Hector Garza along with TNA regulars like Matt Bently (with Traci), Chris Sabin, Sonjay Dutt and others. Fun match.Note: Also available on the "Best Of The X Division Vol. 1" DVDRon Killings, Johnny B. Badd (Marc Mero), Pat Kennedy (Simon Diamond), Erik Watts vs. The Naturals, Kid Kash & Dallas (Lance Hoyt) - Would have been a miss if the crowd wasn't so into it.Mascratita Sagrada vs. Piratita Morgan - Midget match. You'll either like this one or hate this one but like I said early, Dusty was booking so you know where the SmackDown "Junior's division" came from.NWA Tag Team Champions Team Canada vs. 3 Live Cru - If you've seen one 3 Live Kru match then you've seen them all but the Flordia crowd loves them so it helped the match.Trinity vs. Jacqueline - For two women who have been trained in the sport of wrestling, this came off as a match that would happen between people like Torrie Wilson & Candice Michelle.  The interference from Glen Gilberti (Disco Infernio) & Johnny Swinger didn't help either.Monster's Ball: Monty Brown vs. Raven vs. Abyss - Really, this match is just sloppy & all over the place. Honestly, it's just a spot fest to me.Note: Also available on the "Best Of The Bloodiest Brawls" DVDX-Division Champion Petey Williams vs. AJ Styles - If you want to see a good bout from these two, watch Genesis 2005 because this match was really short & again, has too much interference from William's manager to make this seem any good.Note: Also available on the "Best Of The X Division" DVDLast Team Standing Match: America's Most Wanted vs. Triple X - Outside of their cage matches, this is one of their best confrontations together.Ladder Match: NWA World Heavyweight Champion Jeff Jarrett vs. Jeff Hardy - There was some good spots as Hardy is great at hardcore type matches but it seemed like everyone (the wrestlers & announcers) was more concerned about putting over the Outsiders reunion (Scott Hall & Kevin Nash) than having a great match as Scott Hall just kept interfearing & the ending was weak as Nash came out with gutairs for him & Hall and all three guys hit Hardy with it to cost him the match. A suprize appearence from "Macho Man" Randy Savage comes at the end.Note: Also available on the "Enigma: Best Of Jeff Hardy" DVDThis PPV was nice but I would get this as part of the TNA Anthology instead since you get two more DVD's for the price of one.

reviewText: While not a bad PPV it still has it's flaws. The Elimation Last Team Standing match bewteen America's Most Wanted & Triple X was HORRIBLE AS HECK. The Ladder match for the NWA World heavyweight championship between Jeff Jarrett & Jeff Hardy was sloppy but solid. The highlight & showstealer of VR04 was the 20 man X-Division Gauntlet match which was fast-paced,hard-hitting & fun. The Monster's ball match between Monty Brown,Raven & Abyss was a solid & hard-fought brawl and a good reminder of the 1990's ECW. The Midget match between Mascarita Sagrada & Piratita Morgan while not a bad match I still think of it as a "Big Lipped Alligator Moment" The rest are ok. I give this event a 5 out of 10.

reviewText: I have been a wrestling fan since 1996 and have watched all kinds of wrestling. I have a wrestling DVD/VHS collection spanning over 50 all together. This is the most complete and accurate review of this DVD you will find. I hope you find this review helpful; remember to vote helpful or not helpful. (Note-Each DVD I review has a "Match of the DVD" award somewhere in it.)TNA Victory Road 2004TNA finally is able to put on a 3-hour PPV. Here we have their first ever 3-hour PPV in Victory Road 2004. Was it the greatest PPV of all time? No. Was it really even that good at all? Not really. It had its high and low spots like many other PPVs out there.-Disc 1-20 Man X Gauntlet (Match of the DVD)This is a fantastic choice to start off this PPV. You get to see 20 different X-Division stars fighting it out for the World X Cup. Big names like Chris Sabin, Sonjay Dutt, Psychosis, L.A. Park, Kazarian, and so many more are in this match. The match features stars from TNA, Japan, and Mexico. There are too many great spots to name. This loses a point for the ending being weak.RATING- 9/10The Naturals/Kid Kash/Dallas VS Ron Killings/Johnny B. Badd/Erik Watts/Pat KenneyThis was your average tag team match up. No one really got an advantage, and everyone had a time to shine in the ring.RATING- 5/10Piratita Morgan VS Mascaritas SagradaThis is a Mini-Wrestlers match, Mini as in "little people". Many people enjoy this type of match. I personally do not. I still thought it turned out well regardless. It had some very funny moments like the Ref and Morgan praying that Sagrada was okay.RATING- 7/10After this match, Scott Hall makes an appearance and gives his thoughts on the Main Event.NWA World Tag Team ChampionshipsTeam Canada(c) VS 3Live KruNothing really special happens in this match either. It's slightly better than the previous tag match, but still not that great. The ending feels anticlimactic.RATING-6/10In the Pit with Rowdy Roddy Piper featuring Jimmy "Superfly" SnukaTrinity VS JaquelineThe action in this match isn't that bad, it's just that the match lasts around 3-4 minutes. This match could've been much more if given more time.RATING- 4.5/10Monster's BallMonty Brown VS Raven VS AbyssAlthough it was not as brutal as foretold, it was still a nice change of pace in the PPV. All the other Monster's Ball matches have been better than this one. There are some good table spots near the end.RATING- 7.5/10-Disc 2-X-Division Title MatchPetey Williams(c) VS AJ StylesThis is a great X-Division title Match. These two put on a great show. There was a lot of interference, which is never good in a X-Division contest. Some say the match is too short, I feel that it had a perfect length. The ending features one of the sickest Canadian Destroyers I've ever seen.RATING- 8.5/10Last Team StandingTriple X VS America's Most WantedThis is a disgrace if you look at their next match fromTNA Turning Point 2004 Destiny Awaits!. The rules of the match are elimination last man standing. Skipper looks drunk the entire match and stumbles around not doing anything right. Daniels gets eliminated after...nothing at all. He gets pinned and counted out even though no move was hit on him. That left Harris and Skipper. Harris tried to keep Skipper going, but something was wrong with Skipper.RATING- 4/10Ladder MatchNWA World Heavyweight ChampionshipJeff Jarrett(c) VS Jeff HardyThis was your expected good Ladder match from Hardy. It has your good spots and interaction from The Outsiders. I felt the ending was good, even though you could see it coming from a mile away.RATING- 8/10Extras Include-Backstage FootageReplays
